      "acceptanceCriteria": "Achieved level must meet or exceed required level.",
      "rationale": "A formal mesh convergence study was conducted using three mesh densities (coarse, medium, fine) following Richardson extrapolation methodology per ASME V&V 10.1. The grid convergence index (GCI) for construct stiffness was 0.8%, and for yield force was 1.1%, both below the 2% threshold. The medium mesh was selected for production runs, providing an appropriate balance of accuracy and computational cost."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Numerical solver error",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Achieved level must meet or exceed required level.",
      "rationale": "Iterative solver convergence was monitored for all simulations; force and displacement residuals converged below 1e-6. Direct solver cross-checks were performed on three representative models confirming results within 0.1% of iterative solver outputs. No solver divergence or numerical instabilities were observed across the 11-construct ensemble."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Use error",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Achieved level must meet or exceed required level.",
      "rationale": "Model setup procedures are documented in a controlled simulation protocol (SOP-FEA-001 Rev C). Two independent analysts reviewed all boundary conditions, material assignments, and load applications prior to execution. Discrepancies identified during peer review were resolved before results were accepted. Training records confirm both analysts are qualified per the QMS."
