    "actor": "https://uofa.net/nagaraja/actor/credibility-assessment-team",
    "role": "Credibility assessment team",
    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "The FEA modeling framework for non-cannulated pedicle screw compression-bending is accepted for the stated COU. Eleven of thirteen credibility factors were assessed; ten met or exceeded required levels. One factor (Test conditions) achieved level 2 against a required level of 3, reflecting the single-condition test design, which is consistent with ASTM F1717 regulatory practice. Two factors (Relevance of QoIs and Relevance of validation activities to COU) were not assessed, with rationale citing scope limitations; however, no concrete justification for excluding these factors at modelRiskLevel 3 was provided. The overall evidence base, including quantitative V&V 10.1 metrics passing for all three QoIs, was judged sufficient by the team to support regulatory submission.",
